The Independent Elections and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) Monday cleared former Harambee Stars midfielder Mcdonald Mariga to vie in the Kibra Constituency by-election. The nomination of the Jubilee's candidate for the November 7 mini poll was invalidated by the electoral agency last Tuesday because his details were missing from the voters roll of 2017. IEBC chairman Wafula Chebukati announced that Mariga was in the ruling by the dispute resolution committee for the case filed by the football star. More to follow...  